{{liushu|p}} – a horse with its head facing the left, showing a flowing mane in the wind. In the bronze inscriptions, the head was often simplified into an eye ({{zh-m|*目}}). The legs eventually evolved into four dots ({{zh-m|*灬}}, unrelated to {{zh-m|*火}}).

Contrast with {{zh-m|*鹿|deer}}, which saw a very different development, and {{zh-m|*𢊁}} (as in {{zh-m|*薦}}), which is a hybrid: it has the legs of {{lang|zh|馬}} ({{zh-m|*灬}}) but the head of {{zh-m|*鹿}}.

===Etymology===
{{zh-forms|s=马|alt=𫠉,傌,𢒗,𢒠,𢒧,𩡬,𩡮,抹-Sichuan senses,碼-“to bully”}}
