“Horse” – from {{inh|zh|sit-pro|*k-m-raŋ ~ s-raŋ}}. The sense of “big” is derived from “horse”; compare the English uses of {{m|en|horse}}.

For the insect prefix sense, see {{zh-m|*螞}}. It has converged with the sense of “big”.

The surname is popularly known to be prevalent among [[Hui]] Muslims, where it is likely derived from {{der|zh|ar|مُحَمَّد|t=Muhammad}}.

